Section 1:
1 L.D. 561
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 240, L.D. 561, “An Act to Ensure
10 Subsidy Reimbursements for Certain Child Care Providers”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §3737, sub-§6 is enacted to read:
13 6. Reimbursement for subsidies. The department shall reimburse a provider of child
14 care services provided under this chapter for subsidy payments under the Maine Child Care
15 Affordability Program in section 3731-A administered by the department pursuant to rules
16 adopted by the department. Reimbursement under the program to a child care provider must
17 be based on enrollment rather than attendance and may not be reduced or eliminated based
18 on a child's attendance. The department shall adopt rules to implement this subsection.
19 Rules adopted pursuant to this subsection are routine technical rules as defined in Title 5,
20 chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.
21 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
22 allocations are made.
23 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
24 Child Care Services 0563
25 Initiative: Provides funding to reimburse child care providers for subsidy payments based
26 on enrollment rather than attendance under the Maine Child Care Affordability Program
27 for children whose subsidy payments are not covered by federal grant funding.
28 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
29 All Other $75,000 $75,000
30 __________ __________
31 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $75,000 $75,000
3228 '
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
Page 1 - 132LR1485(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 240, L.D. 561
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment removes all the provisions of the bill regarding reimbursement based
33 on generally accepted payment practices. The amendment retains the provisions of the bill
44 that relate to payments based on enrollment rather than attendance. The amendment also
55 adds an appropriations and allocations section.
66 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
77 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR1485(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
